🟢 INTRO — The AI Landscape (30–35 sec)

“Copilot, Gemini, Cursor, Windsurf, Tabnine, Amazon Q —
every developer today has AI writing code.

And then autonomous agents — Devin, SWE-Agent, Claude Code —
planning, debugging, deploying features without a human touching the keyboard.

But here’s the gap.

None of these tools can tell you why the code exists.
What business decision created it.
Or whether what shipped matches what was intended.

That’s Smart SDLC.

The missing memory layer.

Intent → decisions → code → evidence.

Your AI doesn’t just build faster —
it builds the right thing, traceably, at enterprise scale.”

(Pause)

“The world is building faster hammers.
We built the blueprint that proves you built it right.”

“Left screen is the problem. Right screen is the proof.”

(Point to Monitor 1)

🦖 MONITOR 1 — The Evolution Problem (70–80 sec)

“Software delivery evolved like the Jurassic era.

Waterfall — the Brachiosaurus.
Massive centralized knowledge. When the architect left, context fossilized.

Agile — the Velociraptor pack.
Fast, iterative. But context fragmented across sprints.

DevOps — Indominus Rex.
Engineered for velocity. Pipelines automated everything — except understanding.

Now we’re in the AI-augmented era.

Code generation at machine speed.

Velocity is solved.

Coherence is not.

Every era optimized speed.

No era preserved intent.”

(Pause. Slight shift in tone.)

“Smart SDLC is the tamed raptor.

Fast.
Disciplined.
Governed.
Connected.”

(Point to Monitor 2)

🔵 MONITOR 2 — The Proof: Coherence (75–90 sec)

“Here’s what coherence looks like.

One connected delivery graph.

Business intent.
Architecture decision.
Stories.
Commits.
Tests.
Deployment.
Runtime evidence.

One lineage.
Fully traceable.

Now imagine this.

A regulator asks:

‘Why does this trading threshold exist?’

No war room.
No Slack archaeology.

The graph traverses strategy → ADR → code → deployment → evidence — in seconds.

That’s not documentation.

That’s delivery intelligence.

And because it understands intent,
it detects drift,
predicts risk,
and governs AI acceleration.”

🔴 CLOSE — 20 sec

“In 2028, AI will generate most code.

The question won’t be speed.

It will be control.

Smart SDLC connects
Intent → Decision → Code → Evidence.

Auditable.
